able, so let me try setting up a test project to see what naming policies are actually available and whether there's a built-in PascalCase option. Let me just create a test project and see if `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` actually exists in the current .NET version, then build it out from there.","outputTokens":1333,"requestId":"EC0F:E8763:BD1CF4:DD283F:69FE8504"},"id":"5207a1e1-2a0d-40d7-8c83-2acd46439af3","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:51:46.881Z","parentId":"47eaddb8-b907-43b6-b99a-53e13651d391"}
